The All Progressives Congress (APC) delegates have voted in Ahmed Adamu BBK alias Sarkin Ado. The election was held Thursday evening at the event centre of the Potiskum Local Government Secretariat amidst tight security. Potiskum Central Constituency has a total of 35 delegates from the 7 electoral wards of Barebare Bauya Lai Lai, Bolewa ‘A’, Bolewa ‘B’, Yerimaram, Dogo Tebo, Dogo Nini and Hausawa Asibiti respectively. -Advertisement- He won the election with 24 votes out of the 26 cast votes where Dauda Adamu and Fatsuma Umar Bubaram got one vote each. The APC National Officer and Secretary of the Electoral Panel, Bashir Sheriff Kareto counted the ballot and announced the result which produced Ahmed Adamu BBK alias Sarkin Ado as the candidate for the forthcoming 2023 general elections. In his address shortly after the election, the winner thanked all the delegates for their patience, support and cooperation which enabled his success. “I also want to use this medium to appreciate my teeming supporters for the love shown to me, am running short of words in thanking them. I pray God to assist me in discharging this responsibility”. He assured of proper legislation to attract more development in Potiskum Central Constituency when he assumes duty. Supporters of Sarkin Ado after the election embarked on rallies with jubilation and celebrations while escorting the winner to his residence.